EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution authorizing the Speaker to intervene, file an amicus brief, or join an amicus brief on behalf of the Council of the City of New York in the litigation captioned Pelegrin v. New York City Human Resources Administration, for the purpose of defending provisions of the New York City Charter that require city agencies to provide public notice and the opportunity for public comment on proposed new rules and rule changes before adoption.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the Speaker to intervene, file an amicus brief, or join an amicus brief on behalf of the Council of the City of NY in the litigation captioned Pelegrin v. NYC Human Resources Administration.
